# NTI → PMM Integration v1.0

**Subtitle:** How Narrative Tension Feeds the Pantheon Market Mapper  
**Author:** PantheonOS Systems Integration Division  
**Status:** Canonical  
**Version:** 1.0  

---

## 0. Purpose

This document explains how the Narrative Tension Index (NTI) integrates into the Pantheon Market Mapper (PMM) while remaining non-predictive, non-advisory, and narrative-centric.

---

## 1. Relationship Between NTI and NFT

Recall PMM’s scalar:

$$NFT = \frac{(N \times Q \times I \times L)}{V}$$

In the PMM context, we identify: $N = NTI / 100$.

NFT is then:

$$NFT = \left(\frac{NTI}{100}\right) \cdot \frac{Q \cdot I \cdot L}{V}$$

---

## 2. Data Flow

```text
Raw Signals
      │
      ▼
Narrative Parsing
      │
      ▼
NTI Engine
      │
      ▼
Normalize NTI
      │
      ▼
Pass N into PMM
      │
      ▼
PMM Output
